  {
    "id": 609,
    "question": "The interior angles of a quadrilateral are (x + 15)°, (2x - 45)°, ( x - 30)° and (x + 10)°. Find the value of the least interior angle.",
    "option": {
      "a": "112°",
      "b": "102°",
      "c": "82°",
      "d": "52°",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "d",
    "solution": "(x + 15)o + (2x - 45)o + (x + 10)o = (2n - 4)90o\n\nwhen n = 4\n\nx + 15o + 2x - 45o + x - 30o + x + 10o = (2 x 4 - 4) 90o\n\n5x - 50° = (8 - 4)90°\n\n5x - 50° = 4 x 90° = 360°\n\n5x = 360° + 50°\n\n5x = 410°\n\nx = 410°/5\n\n= 82°\n\nHence, the value of the least interior angle is (x - 30°)\n\n= (82 - 30)°\n\n= 52°",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2010"
  },
