      "b": "200",
      "c": "30",
      "d": "50",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "b",
    "solution": "A committee of 2 women and 3 men can be chosen from 6 men and 5 women, in <sup>5</sup>C<sub>2</sub> x <sup>6</sup>C<sub>3</sub> ways\n\n= 5!/(5−2)!2! × 6!/(6−3)!3!\n\n= 5!/3!2! × 6!/3×3!\n\n= 5×4×3!/3!×2! × 6×5×4×3!/3!×3!\n\n= 5×4/1×2 × 6×5×4/1×2×3\n\n= 10 x (6×20)/6\n\n= 200",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2010"
